node.text:
In one encounter with God, everything can change. Regardless of your background or what you are going through, the God of revival and awakening is ready to meet you right where you are at.

We would love for you to join us for our 7th Annual Young Saints Conference [On-Campus and Online] on October 22-23 as we pursue a fresh encounter so that we may once again chase after all that God has in store for us. It is your destiny, as the youth of this generation, to be awakened again and carry power into the world. Speakers will include Ben Fitzgerald, Tom Crandall, and more! Worship from YS Worship.

node.title: Young Saints Conference 2021 - Revival is Now

node.text:
The Word of the Lord says God created man in His own image and called it good. God created a clear, powerful purpose for manhood. Men, true masculinity was built into your DNA. Yet for many people, it has been blurred by conflicting messages from the world around us. We live in a time where men are looking for the codebook to manhood.

At BraveCo Men's Conference, our hope is to answer your hard questions, get in the foxhole with you, restore the narrative of manhood, and release you into the masculinity you were born to carry.

Join us for our first-ever BraveCo Men’s Conference in partnership with Bethel Church, featuring speakers John Eldredge, Kris Vallotton, Brian Johnson, Danny Silk, Jason Vallotton, and Aaron Zint. This is not your typical Men’s Conference, but instead features opportunities to build a brotherhood as well as interactive experiences with professional horse trainer Todd Pierce, who will break a wild horse to demonstrate how Jesus pursues, heals, and becomes one with us as a Father.

Aug 25 - 27, 2021. Register now for in-person and online tickets at bethel.com/braveco

node.text: “Higher than the highest heavens—that’s how high Your tender mercy extends! Greater than the grandeur of heaven above is the greatness of Your loyal love, towering over all who fear You and bow down before You! Farther than from a sunrise to a sunset—that’s how far You’ve removed our guilt from us.” - Psalm 103:11-12

node.text: What an incredible final day of this year’s BraveCo Men’s conference! Here’s a recap of some of the day’s speakers and events. #BraveCoConference2021

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Bethel Church on August 27, 2021 tagging @kvministries. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'YO U RE RN R RY YOU WERE BORN FOR GLORY WE Bo FC GLO KRIS VALLOTTON'.

node.text: Tonight, @kvministries shared a deeply powerful word about the truth that this life, and the legacies we invest in now, will shape the course of family, Church, and global history. We aren’t living for ourselves, we’re living to be a people who battle giants now so that those after us won’t have to. #BraveCoConference2021

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bethel Church on August 27, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'You won't heal until you become vulnerable, start getting rid of your secrets, access the pain hiding inside of you, and reject passivity. AARON ZINT'.

node.text:
Today, Aaron Zint gave a vitally important message about what we really need to thrive. He focused on three key areas: connection, healing for pain, and intentionality with ourselves and our lives, and with those around us. Here are some key questions to ask yourself:

1. Am I truly known by people in my life? Who is close enough in my life to really “see” who I am?

2. What secrets am I still hiding? Where have I given my secrets power over my identity, self-esteem, choices, etc.? 

3. What am I avoiding? Where am I being passive and why?

Taking time to engage with these questions and going on the journey towards wholeheartedness will change your life! #BraveCoConference2021

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Bethel Church on August 27, 2021 tagging @brianjohnsonm. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text: “Love leans in first. It listens long enough to understand why. It hears what a person fought through to get to where they are. It listens until it can hear with empathy.” - Brian Johnson @brianjohnsonm #BraveCoConference2021

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Bethel Church on August 27, 2021 tagging @jayvallotton. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'THERE ARE BURDENS THAT WE HAVE IN THIS LIFE. BUTABURS BUT A BURDEN IS SOMETHING THAT, IF CARRIED ALONE WILL DAMAGE YOU YOU WEREN'T MEANT TO CARRY BURDENS ALONE. JASON VALLOTTON'.

node.text: This morning’s word from @jayvallotton focused on the power of your story and the importance of accepting the invitation to run towards wholeness with a community of brothers. This conference is full of life, wisdom, and the call to build together to see families, cities, and nations transformed by wholehearted living! #BraveCoConference2021

node.text: The first half of this year's BraveCo Conference has been incredible, from horsebreaking to BBQ, to experiencing God's presence in worship and pursuing wholeheartedness! #BraveCoConference2021

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Bethel Church on August 26, 2021 tagging @wildatheart. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'MASCULINITY INITY IS STRENGTH IN THE SERVICE OF LOVE JOHN ELDREDGE'.

node.text:
"The essence of masculinity is strength on behalf of others. Masculinity is strength in the service of love." - John Eldredge

It's been such an honor to hear from John Eldredge during this year's BraveCo Conference. From charging men to grow and heal, to leading through practical steps to move into wholeheartedness and embracing the adventure men were born for, today has been an encouraging, courage-filling day! #bravecoconference2021

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Bethel Church on August 26, 2021 tagging @dannylovingonpurpose. May be an image of text that says 'THERE ISN'T ANYTHING MORE ENCOURAGING THAN WATCHING MEN TOGETHER TO RUN BE A TEAM, TO BEA BE SQUAD TO BE A BROTHERHOOD. DANNY DANNYSILK SILK'.

node.text: BraveCo is focused fully on creating a movement of men who run together! This morning, @dannylovingonpurpose brought an awesome message about what it means to be men of great heart, who build courageously, love well, and give that courage and love to others. Who are you running with? Let us know in the comments! 🎉 #BraveCoConference2021

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Bethel Church on August 26, 2021 tagging @braveco.men. May be an image of 1 person, standing, horse and text that says 'BRAVECO MEN'S CONFERENCE'.

node.text: Last night, our first session for this year’s BraveCo Men’s Conference featured a horse breaking by Todd Pierce! This powerful illustration of God’s love and leading in our lives is captivating, and left an lasting impression on all of us!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Bethel Church on August 25, 2021 tagging @jayvallotton, and @braveco.men. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'PURSUE WHOLENESS'.

node.text: Tonight is the first night of our first-ever BraveCo Men’s Conference! The heart of BraveCo is to create a collective of men pursuing wholeness, purpose, and brotherhood. Over the course of the next three days, lifelong connections will be forged, hearts will be restored, and lives will be changed. As you join us, we pray that you too will experience the breakthrough, healing, and wholeness! #BraveCoConference2021
